The key innovation is the **Relational Optimal Transport (ROT) objective**, which uses Earth Mover’s Distance (EMD) to align predicted relation distributions with observed co-occurrence patterns, incorporating semantic costs between KB relations for better generalization. An alternative **spectral embedding** method is also suggested, using the co-occurrence matrix’s global structure via differentiable spectral techniques.

